    <abstract>
      <t>A slice policy is a policy construct that enables instantiation of mechanisms in support of IETF network slice specific control and data plane behaviors on select topological elements. This document defines a YANG data model for the management of slice policies on slice policy capable nodes and controllers in IP/MPLS networks.</t>
